lead_paragraph: Don JOSE DE LA CONCHA, the Captain General whose administration has fallen in these troubles times is by birth a Brazillas, the son of a General who espoused the patriotic cause in Brazil, and who was killed in the course of the struggle. There are three or four brothers CONCHA, I believe, one of whom has acquired great power and influence is Spain, and who has of course raised his family with himself.
